%S A391943 330,364,397,426,430,463,496,512,530,563,576,596,629,640,663,696,704,
%T A391943 729,762,768,768,795,829,862,895,896,928,962,995,1024,1024,1028,1061,
%U A391943 1094,1128,1161,1194,1227,1261,1294,1327,1360,1393,1427,1460,1493,1526,1536,1559,1593,1626,1659,2048,2048
%N A391943 Binary widths of the RSA numbers A391940.
%C A391943 From _M. F. Hasler_, May 21 2026: (Start)
%C A391943 The RSA numbers of the Factoring Challenge in 1991 were labeled according to their number of decimal digits, RSA-100 to RSA-500 and RSA-617. The RSA numbers for the 2001 extension of the challenge were labeled according to the number of binary digits, a(n) = 576, 640, 704, 768, 896, 1024, 1536 and 2048. Of these, only RSA-576 and RSA-640 had been factored when the challenge ended in 2007.
%C A391943 See A391940 for more information about what numbers are listed and in which order.
%C A391943 Duplicate values are a(n) = a(n+1) = 768, 1024 and 2048 for n = 20, 30 and 53. (End)
%H A391943 <a href="/index/Bi#binary">Index entries for sequences related to binary expansion of n</a>.
%F A391943 a(n) = A070939(A391940(n)).
%o A391943 (PARI) A391943(n)=exponent(A391940(n))+1 \\ _M. F. Hasler_, May 21 2026
%Y A391943 Cf. A070939 (bit count), A391940 (RSA numbers).
%Y A391943 Cf. also A391944.
%K A391943 nonn,base,fini,full,changed
%O A391943 1,1
%A A391943 _Antti Karttunen_, Dec 28 2025
